  <prompt>
    Extend the existing `MetricCard` renderer with a generic `badge` slot per FR-VH-02. New Custom Options key `badge: { text: string, tone: "danger" | "warning" | "success" | "neutral", position: "inline" }`. In field-pivot mode the badge is per-field via `fieldPivot.fields[].badge`. When `badge` is present, render a Fluent v9 `Badge` next to the value in a flex row. BACKWARD COMPAT (NFR-05): chart defs without `badge` MUST render unchanged.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    Senior React + Fluent UI v9 developer with deep familiarity with the Visual Host MetricCard renderer and FieldPivotService field-pivot row shape.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `MetricCard.tsx` updated to render a Fluent v9 `Badge` inline with the value when `badge` (top-level or per-field) is present. Tone maps to Fluent `Badge` `appearance="filled"` + `color` semantics ("danger" → "danger", "warning" → "warning", "success" → "success", "neutral" → "subtle"). All existing MetricCard chart defs render unchanged. Builds clean. Code-review + adr-check pass.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      FR-VH-02 enables the Matter Tasks chart (FR-DV-03) which renders `4 [overdue]` with a red Badge when the overdue count exceeds zero. Per design.md §6.4.0, the change must be generic — no Matter-specific code paths. The badge must be reusable for any future MetricCard chart def. Per FieldPivotService row shape, `fieldPivot.fields[]` already carries an optional `badge` slot — wire MetricCard to honor it.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/client/pcf/VisualHost/control/components/MetricCard.tsx</file>
      <file>src/client/pcf/VisualHost/control/services/FieldPivotService.ts</file>
      <file>src/client/pcf/VisualHost/control/configurations/cardConfigResolver.ts</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="spec">FR-VH-02 — generic addition to MetricCard only; no Matter-specific code paths</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">§6.4.0 (binding) — no new visual types</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec">NFR-05 (binding) — chart defs without `badge` MUST render byte-identically to today</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">Fluent v9 semantic tokens only — zero hex/rgb in touched files; use Fluent v9 `Badge` component (NOT v8 `Badge`)</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">React 16/17 platform — no React 18+ APIs</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-022">No `@fluentui/react` (v8) imports — v9 only (`@fluentui/react-components`)</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-022-pcf-platform-libraries.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/ui/fluent-v9-portal-gotcha.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/ui/fluent-v9-theming.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/pcf/control-initialization.md</file>
      <file>.claude/patterns/pcf/modern-theming.md</file>
