    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Fluent v9 Badge" location="@fluentui/react-components">
        Import `Badge` and use `appearance="filled"` with `color` prop for tone. Avoid manual styling.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="FieldPivot row shape" location="src/client/pcf/VisualHost/control/services/FieldPivotService.ts">
        Each resolved row is `{ label, value, badge? }`. Wire MetricCard to honor the per-field `badge` when present.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step order="0">Step 0.5: Invoke `Skill fluent-v9-component` — binding per design.md §6.0. Load Fluent v9 patterns.</step>
    <step order="1">Read MetricCard.tsx + FieldPivotService.ts + cardConfigResolver.ts to anchor the existing contract and identify the NFR-05 baseline.</step>
    <step order="2">Update MetricCard options type in cardConfigResolver.ts (or shared types) with `badge?: { text: string, tone: "danger" | "warning" | "success" | "neutral", position: "inline" }`. Confirm `fieldPivot.fields[].badge` is already typed in FieldPivotService row shape; if not, add it there too.</step>
    <step order="3">In MetricCard.tsx, after resolving the value, check for badge in this order: per-field `fieldPivot.fields[].badge` (field-pivot mode) → top-level `badge`. If present, render Fluent v9 `&lt;Badge appearance="filled" color={mapTone(tone)}&gt;{text}&lt;/Badge&gt;` next to the value in a flex row with `tokens.spacingHorizontalS` gap.</step>
    <step order="4">Tone-mapping helper: "danger" → "danger", "warning" → "warning", "success" → "success", "neutral" → "subtle". Local helper in MetricCard.tsx (do not export — keep generic + co-located).</step>
    <step order="5">Backward-compat verification: re-render every MetricCard chart def from the task-001 inventory. Capture screenshots in `notes/spikes/visualhost-regression-evidence/metriccard-baseline-021/`. Pixel-diff must be ZERO.</step>
    <step order="6">Build verification: `npm run build:prod` in VisualHost. Zero TypeScript errors. Bundle delta noted.</step>
    <step order="6.5">FULL rigor quality gates: invoke `Skill code-review` then `Skill adr-check` — block until both pass. Verify ADR-021 token usage and ADR-022 React/v9 boundaries.</step>
    <step order="7">Update TASK-INDEX.md: 021 → ✅. Update current-task.md to next pending task (likely 022 — sequential because shared file).</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
